	%p
		5.1 Seat Belts and Child Restraints - Member is responsible for:
	%p
		a. Complying with all applicable seat belt and child restraint laws;
	%p
		b. Protecting all children by properly using any child passenger restraint system that complies with the Motor Vehicle Safety Standards in the jurisdiction where the trip is initiated and where the Zoomcar vehicle is driven during such trip.

	%p.zoom.f-b.size-16
		6. Securing Zoomcar Vehicles
	%p
		6.1 Each time the member parks a Zoomcar Vehicle (either at the end of the reservation or during), the member is responsible for securing the vehicle.
	%p
		a. Windows must be closed and
		The central locking system must be enabled using the smart phone app or the SMS command). If the car is outside of cell phone range, and the car cannot be locked through the phone command system, the user must remove the key and lock the car manually.  Member will be responsible for any fees or charges associated with a failure to perform these steps.
	%p
		6.2 The Member must remove the navigation tablet computer from its dashboard mount and place securely in the glove box, locking such compartment once securely fastened.  Failure to secure the vehicle or tablet will result in financial penalties in case of preventable theft or vandalism according to the Fee Schedule.
	%p
		6.3 Zoomcar encourages all its customers to take full responsibility of their belongings. In case of any Member claims to have left back any luggage or any phones or personal music devices inadvertently in the Zoomcar vehicle after the Member completes his/her reservation, Zoomcar shall endeavor to locate the lost belongings on a "best-effort" basis provided the Member notifies Zoomcar of the same within reasonable time, but Zoomcar shall not be held responsible for such loss or damage.

	%p.zoom.f-b.size-16
		7. Eligible (Reimbursable) Expenses
	%p
		7.1 An "Eligible Expense" is defined as (a) any fuel related expense (b) an expense incurred by the Member for minor (under INR 1000) routine maintenance on Zoomcar vehicles, such as new wiper blades, light bulbs, or windshield-washer fluid, etc. and (c) any expense in excess of INR 1000 that is authorized in advance by a Zoomcar Representative. If a Member pays for an Eligible Expense, he or she must keep the receipt and note on it the time it was made during the reservation period. The Member must print his or her name on the receipt and give a physical hard copy of the receipt to the Zoomcar vehicle attendant after their reservation.  Zoomcar will reimburse the member or credit the member's account.  No reimbursement or credit will be given without a receipt, or if the receipt is submitted 30 days or more from the reservation date.

	%p.zoom.f-b.size-16
