	%p
		8.1 Zoomcar will perform all necessary and required routine maintenance on all of its vehicles. However, Members are responsible for the cleanliness of vehicles and are expected to assist in helping Zoomcar to maintain the driving safety and performance of the vehicle, in particular during longer reservations or when the vehicle indicates that service or maintenance is required.
	%p
		8.2 Vehicles may require Roadside Assistance from time to time. Zoomcar makes reasonable best efforts to provide Roadside Assistance support in all cases.  If, however, a Member's need for Roadside Assistance results from a breach of these Terms and Conditions, the Member may be charged for the full costs of the service.
	%p
		8.3 Inappropriate noises or driving feel, including but not limited to warning lamps, indicators, inappropriate sounds or smells, or performance changes must be reported to Zoomcar as soon as noted. Failure to report such irregularities during the use of a Zoomcar vehicle may result in such Member's immediate suspension or termination of the Member's Contract.
	%p
		8.4 Tobacco use is absolutely prohibited in Zoomcar vehicles.  Members are subject to fees if evidence of smoking, chewing, or dipping is found in Zoomcar vehicles or complained of by a Member using the vehicle immediately following the Member’s reservation.
	%p
		8.5 Burning any substance is absolutely prohibited in Zoomcar vehicles.  This includes, but is not limited to tobacco, other drugs, and incense.
	%p
		8.6 Pets are absolutely prohibited in Zoomcar vehicles, except for those vehicles designated “pet friendly”.  Members are subject to fees if evidence of pets is found in Zoomcar vehicles or complained of by a Member using the vehicle immediately following the Member’s reservation.

